In [7]: def othogonal_fuc(array_test):

   ...: import numpy as np

   ...: from scipy import linalg

   ...: list_1=[]

   ...: v_direkt=0

   ...: m,n=array_test.shape

   ...: for i in range(m):

   ...: if i ==0:

   ...: list_1.append((array_test[i]/linalg.norm(array_test[i])))

   ...: else:

   ...: v_direkt=sum([(np.dot(list_1[j-1],array_test[i])/((linalg.norm(list_1[j-1]))**2))*list_1[j-1] for j in range(1,i+1) ])

   ...: v_i=array_test[i]-v_direkt

   ...: list_1.append(v_i/linalg.norm(v_i))

   ...: return list_1

   ...:
